,"death":{"year":1855,"city":"Cambridge","state":"Massachusetts"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00151","mother_id":"X01018"},"marriages":[],"tags":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[],"slug":"susannah-newton-1779"},"HD0007":{"id":"HD0007","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":4,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1699,"month":5,"day":14,"city":"Milford","state":"Connecticut"},"parents":{"father_id":"H00011","mother_research_notes":"Sarah Welch Fowler, second wife of Samuel Newton","mother_id":"X00097","mother_name":"Sarah Welch Fowler"},"sources":[{"short":"Caroline Gaylord Newton 1914"},{"short":"Families of Early Milford","platform":"Ancestry.com"}],"death":{"year":1769,"month":2,"day":24,"city":"Durham","state":"Connecticut"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I00026","children_ids":["H00147","H00148","H00149","H00150","H00151","X00027"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1724}],"marriage_date":{"year":1724,"notes":"Married early 1724; deed dated June 18, 1724 gives \"Abner Newton of Milford and Mary his wife\""},"primary_residence":{"city":"Durham","state":"Connecticut","notes":"Removed from Milford to Durham, settling there in late 1724. Deed of July 1724 calls him \"Abner Newton of Milford\"; deed of December 1724 calls him \"Abner Newton, late of Milford, now of Durham.\""},"tags":["durham_newton"],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Abner Newton","first_name":"Abner","last_name":"Newton","married_names":[]},"landmarks":[],"residence":{"city":"Durham","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST022"}],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Half-brother shared same first name, Abner","body":"This Abner Newton was born 1699 to Samuel Newton's second wife Sarah Welch Fowler — distinguishing him from his half-brother Abner Newton baptized May 1689, who had been born to Samuel's first wife Martha Fenn ten years earlier. The repeated Abner name across both marriages was uncommon. The 1699 Abner became the documented ancestor of the Durham Newton branch — earning the 'durham_newton' tag in this entry."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"1724 Milford-to-Durham move; wife sold inherited share","body":"In 1724 Abner Newton and Mary Burwell removed from Milford to Durham Connecticut — and on the move Mary sold her own inherited property, a quarter share of a dwelling house and home-lot in Milford, to Susannah Burwell (widow of John Burwell) for eighty pounds. Per the deed boundaries this was the homestead of the first John Burwell, occupied since 1639. Mary had kept a share in her family's original Milford homestead until the day she left for Durham."},{"number":3,"category":"character","header":"Son Roger received Alice Newton's Yale bequest","body":"Abner's son Roger Newton was the beneficiary of Alice Newton's ca.1740 conditional Yale bequest — establishing the family's Yale-funded ministerial track. Roger graduated Yale 1758 and served fifty-six years as minister at Greenfield Massachusetts until 1816 — one of the longest continuous American pastorates of the Revolutionary-Republican era."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM569"},"slug":"abner-newton-1699"},"I00026":{"id":"I00026","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1698,"month":8,"day":28},"death":{"year":1759,"month":4,"day":9},"parents":{"father_id":"X00027","mother_id":"X00028"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"HD0007","children_ids":["H00147","H00148","H00149","H00150","H00151","X00027"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1724}],"sources":[{"short":"Families of Early Milford, Connecticut","platform":"Ancestry.com"}],"gender":"male","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":1,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Mary Burwell","first_name":"Mary","last_name":"Burwell","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"mary-burwell-1698"},"H00011":{"id":"H00011","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":3,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"is_progenitor":false},"birth":{"year":1646,"month":10,"day":20,"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1708,"month":12,"day":10,"city":"Milford","county":"New Haven","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM005","plot_notes":"Oldest part of the Milford Cemetery. FindAGrave #29848117."},"parents":{"father_id":"I00003","mother_id":"H00003"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I00008","children_ids":["H00039","H00040","H00041","H00043","H00044"],"marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1697,"date_year":1669,"date_month":3,"date_day":14},{"children_ids":["H00045","HD0007"],"spouse_id":"X00097","marriage_number":2,"date_year":1697,"date_month":1,"date_day":1}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00029","display_label":"Their wives were half-sisters — Fenn family.","link_text":"William Hooker"}],"tags":["king_philips_war","politician"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 11"},{"short":"Caroline Gaylord Newton 1914"}],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":2,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"is_placeholder":false,"former_ids":[],"baptism":{},"residence":{"country":"United States"},"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"research_tags":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"military","header":"Militia ensign in King Philip's War","body":"When King Philip's War broke out in 1675, Samuel was appointed ensign in the Milford militia at roughly age 29. He served through the war and its recurring aftermath of Indian skirmishes, rising to captain of the Milford militia by 1698."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"Represented Milford fifteen times in the General Court","body":"He represented Milford in fifteen sessions of the Connecticut General Court between 1691 and 1703 — a span of sustained civic service that ran alongside his captaincy of the militia. His father Roger Newton Sr. had helped found the town's church."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Thomas Hooker left him £10 in his will","body":"He was nine months old when his grandfather Rev. Thomas Hooker died in 1647. Thomas's will left a £10 legacy to him — a substantial inheritance for a Hooker grandchild born during the Hartford founding."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"His wife and cousin's wife were Fenn half-sisters","body":"His wife Martha Fenn's half-sister Susanna married William Hooker — Samuel's first cousin. The Fenn family thus connected to the Hooker tree twice in the same generation through different lines."},{"number":5,"category":"family","header":"A second marriage to a soldier's widow","body":"After Martha Fenn died, Samuel married Sarah Welch Fowler, widow of John Fowler, who had been killed taking an Indian fort in 1693. Their son Abner bore a name found nowhere else in the Newton or Hooker line."}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"artworks":[],